{"type":"message","id":"ecfae968","parentId":"e1da6e8e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:22:54.874Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_d0381a19-e1c0-4b44-bd21-9bdd802ca6d4","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Dawn Restore Instructions — Fresh Machine Setup\n\n## Overview\nThis restore kit rebuilds Dawn (OpenClaw assistant) on a machine with no WSL, no Ollama, nothing.\n\n---\n\n## Step 1: Windows Setup\n\n### 1a. Install WSL2\nOpen PowerShell as Administrator:\n```powershell\nwsl --install\n```\nRestart machine when prompted.\n\n### 1b. Install Ubuntu (WSSL2 default)\nAfter restart, Ubuntu will open. Set username/password.\n\n```bash\nsudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Install Ollama (Windows side)\n\n### 2a. Download Ollama\n```powershell\n# In PowerShell (run as admin)\nirm https://ollama.com/install.ps1 | iex\n```\n\n### 2b. Pull models\n```powershell\nollama pull minimax-m2.7\nollama pull minimax-m2.7:cloud\nollama pull llama3.2:3b\nollama pull gemma3:27b\nollama pull nemotron-3-super\n```\n\nOllama runs at `http://localhost:11434` — WSL2 can reach it via the Windows host IP.\n\n### 2c. Allow Ollama from WSL (optional, more reliable)\nIn PowerShell as admin, create inbound rule on port 11434, or:\n```powershell\nnetsh advfirewall firewall add rule name=\"Ollama\" dir=in action=allow protocol=TCP localport=11434\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 3: Install Node.js 18+ (in WSL)\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E bash -\nsudo apt install -y nodejs\nnode --version  # should be v22.x\nnpm --version\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 4: Install OpenClaw (in WSL)\n\n```bash\nnpm install -g openclaw\nopenclaw --version  # confirm\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 5: Configure OpenClaw (in WSL)\n\n```bash\n# Initialize config\nopenclaw configure\n\n# When asked:\n#   Gateway token: use \"ollama\" (short — security risk, change later)\n#   Model: select ollama provider\n#   Default model: minimax-m2.7:cloud\n#   WSL browser: yes (WSLg available)\n\n# Link WhatsApp (after first run):\nopenclaw channels add whatsapp\n# Scan QR code with phone\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 6: Restore Workspace Files\n\n### 6a. Copy restore kit\nCopy the `Dawn-Restore/` folder from OneDrive to:\n```\nC:\\Users\\<YourName>\\OneDrive\\Apps\\Dawn-Restore\\\n```\n\n### 6b. Clone git repo (or copy from restore)\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw\ngit clone https://github.com/tiny4lurv/dawn-workspace.git ~/.openclaw/workspace\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\n```\n\n### 6c. Copy memory and config\n```bash\nBACKUP=\"C:/Users/<YourName>/OneDrive/Apps/Dawn-Restore\"\ncp \"$BACKUP/memory/\"* ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ 2>/dev/null || true\ncp \"$BACKUP/openclaw.json\" ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n```\n\n### 6d. OpenClaw auth for Google Workspace (defer for now)\n```bash\ngws auth login\n# Follow OAuth flow — requires Google Cloud project setup\n```\n\n---\n\n## Step 7: Verify Install\n\n```bash\nopenclaw status\nopenclaw gateway start\nopenclaw chat\n```\n\n---\n\n## What Lives Where\n\n| Item | Path |\n|------|------|\n| OpenClaw config | `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` |\n| Workspace (git-tracked) | `~/.openclaw/workspace/` |\n| Daily memory | `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` |\n| Long-term memory | `~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md` |\n| Ollama (Windows) | `http://localhost:11434` |\n| Screenshots | `C:\\Users\\<You>\\OpenClawScreenshots\\` |\n| TinyBackUp | `C:\\Users\\<You>\\TinyBackUp\\` |\n\n---\n\n## WSLg Browser (Visible Chromium)\n\nWSLg is built into WSL2 — no extra X server needed.\n\n```bash\n# Start visible Chromium\nexport DISPLAY=:0\nexport ELECTRON_OZONE_PLATFORM_HINT=auto\nnohup /usr/bin/chromium-browser \\\n  --no-sandbox \\\n  --remote-debugging-port=18801 \\\n  --user-data-dir=/tmp/chromium-visible \\\n  > /tmp/chromium_visible.log 2>&1 &\n```\n\nCDP port: 18801\n\n---\n\n## Key Files in This Restore Kit\n\n- `openclaw.json` — full OpenClaw configuration\n- `memory/` — daily memory files (Mar–Apr 2026)\n- `workspace/` — git-tracked workspace (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, MEMORY.md, etc.)\n- `GIT_REPO.md` — git remote and last commit info\n\n---\n\n## Common Issues\n\n### Ollama not reachable from WSL\n```bash\n# In WSL, test:\ncurl http://localhost:11434/api/version\n# If fails, try Windows host IP:\ncurl http://$(cat /etc/resolv.conf | grep nameserver | awk '{print $2}'):11434/api/version\n```\n\n### WhatsApp not linking\n- Check phone has Signal/internet\n- Use `openclaw channels list` to see status\n- QR code expires in ~60 seconds — be ready\n\n### Gateway won't start\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway stop\nopenclaw gateway start\nopenclaw status\n```\n","path":"/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Apps/Dawn-Restore/RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":20385,"output":1318,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775532174870}}
