{"type":"message","id":"4e987bc5","parentId":"78ab89aa","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:15.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_f143bae9-f0ec-49d8-98ae-0e80ebb67153","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":29839,"output":393,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775573295483}}
{"type":"message","id":"e61469c9","parentId":"4e987bc5","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:15.529Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_f143bae9-f0ec-49d8-98ae-0e80ebb67153","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-06 — Session Log\n\n## Dusk VPS — Setup & Access\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Dusk's gateway was DEAD for ~6 hours (10:49 UTC, crashed after WhatsApp conflict)\n- Restarted successfully: `systemctl --user start openclaw-gateway`\n- Running on: `0.0.0.0:18789` (publicly accessible with token)\n- Token: `dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2`\n\n### Ports found on Dusk\n- `18789` — Gateway WebSocket (0.0.0.0)\n- `18791` — Control UI (localhost only)\n- `80/443` — Caddy web server (proxies to gateway)\n\n### Caddyfile (Dusk)\n```\n:80 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\n:443 { reverse_proxy localhost:18789 }\n```\n→ If domain pointed to Dusk's IP, Control UI would work through Caddy.\n\n### WhatsApp Conflict Resolved\n- Dusk had WhatsApp ENABLED in config → fighting Dawn for primary (+27763674298)\n- Caused 440 conflicts on Dawn's WhatsApp\n- FIXED: Disabled Dusk's WhatsApp via config edit:\n```bash\nc['channels']['whatsapp']['enabled'] = False\n```\n- Restarted gateway: `systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway`\n- Dawn's WhatsApp stabilized after this\n\n### Access Methods for Dusk\n1. **TUI via SSH tunnel:**\n```bash\nssh -N -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 Tiny4Lurv@204.168.204.198\nopenclaw tui --url ws://127.0.0.1:18789 --token dusk_gateway_token_R8k3mNpQ2\n```\n2. **Web UI:** Needs domain + Caddy setup (not currently configured)\n3. **WhatsApp:** DISABLED — would need separate phone number or linked-device auth to re-enable\n\n---\n\n## Dawn WhatsApp — 428 Flapping\n- 428 = \"Precondition Required Connection Terminated\" — WhatsApp Web session expiring\n- Reconnecting successfully every time\n- Cause: long idle periods (no messages for 30+ min)\n- NOT the 440 conflict — that was Dusk's WhatsApp fighting Dawn\n- Status: annoying but not critical\n\n---\n\n## Nava LinkedIn Series\n\n### Post 1 — Finalized\n- LI, X (3-tweet + 2-tweet), FB (full version), visual concept (split panel) — all saved\n- **STATUS:** Pending review from Tiny + Yosef before posting\n- File: `nava-linkedin-series/POST-1-draft.md`\n\n### Post 2 — NavaSM Draft Returned\n- NavaSM drafted facility leader angle (~300 words)\n- Key points: $40,038 turnover cost, 32-65% agency markup, KPMG NATHO study, 11 states with rate cap legislation\n- Voice: sharp, math-forward, \"nuance doesn't break the cycle\" pivot\n- **STATUS:** Awaiting Tiny review\n\n### Post 3 — Not yet drafted\n- Clinician perspective + international pipeline as structural fix\n\n---\n\n## Restore Kit Built (02:00 UTC)\n**Location:** `C:\\Users\\Tiny4Lurv\\OneDrive\\Apps\\Dawn-Restore\\`\n- `dawn-workspace-backup.tar.gz` (150MB)\n- `RESTORE_INSTRUCTIONS.md`\n- `OPENCLAW_REINSTALL.md`\n- `GIT_REPO.md`\n- Committed: `a4479ca`\n\n---\n\n## TrnsBank\n- Count: 175 (threshold: 200)\n- Next analysis due when Tiny locks bank\n\n---\n\n## Apr 6 — NavaSM Architecture Review\n\n### CustomGPT Downloaded (NavaSM = Social Media Strategy Bot)\n- File: \"Travel Nursing_ A Systemic Failure.odt\" — CustomGPT definition downloaded\n- CustomGPT IS NavaSM (NavaSocialMedia) — confirmed today\n- NavaAA = NavaArticleArchitect (blog articles)\n- Architecture now clear: NavaSM = social strategy/copy, NavaAA = long-form\n\n### CustomGPT's Strategic Framework (Gold Standard)\nThe CustomGPT has three canonical personas — this is the reference architecture for NavaSM rewrite:\n1. **Yosef (CEO)** — financial/ROI, \"Reclaimix\" philosophy, stop-the-bleed angle\n2. **Nava Corporate** — structural critique, \"mail-sorting agencies\" framing, gentleman sniper\n3. **Tiny (Personal)** — data/volume trap, \"Robots vs Robots\" AI arms race, UK English, no em-dashes\n\n### CustomGPT Workflow (Gold Standard)\n1. Phase 1: Concept & Angle — propose 2-3 persona options with hooks + visual direction\n2. Approval gate — wait for Tiny to pick direction before drafting\n3. Phase 2: Draft copy + visual concept\n\n### Key Strengths from CustomGPT (to incorporate into NavaSM SKILL.md)\n- Visual direction per post (infographic concepts alongside copy)\n- Competitor references in angle framing (Reclaimix, Delta Coverage)\n- \"Mail-sorting agencies,\" \"leaky bucket,\" \"volume trap,\" \"arbitrage\" — sharp vocab\n- Pre-draft approval gate\n- Three content personas (not five platform personas)\n\n### Gap: Current NavaSM SKILL.md is outdated\n- Uses five platform personas (LI/X/FB) instead of three content personas\n- No visual direction protocol\n- No pre-draft approval gate\n- No competitor framing vocabulary\n- Needs full rewrite to match CustomGPT architecture\n\n### Open Questions (awaiting Tiny's answers)\n1. Should the three personas (Yosef, Corporate, Tiny) be canonical going forward?\n2. Should visual direction be standard output for every NavaSM post?\n3. Confirm the concept-first → approval → draft workflow is the permanent standard?\n\n### Files Referenced Today\n- CustomGPT definition: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Travel Nursing_ A Systemic Failure.odt`\n- Strategic feedback: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Strategic Feedback on Marketing Angles.odt`\n- Current NavaSM skill: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/navasm/SKILL.md`\n- NavaAA system prompt: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/nava-writing/navaaa-system-prompt.md`\n\n### Sprint Check-in — 10:03 UTC\n- TrnsBank: 175 (waiting for Tiny lock, under 200)\n- Post 2 + 3 still pending\n- NavaSM rewrite: awaiting Tiny's answers on 3 questions above\n- Blog corpus 5 no-bylines: still awaiting Tiny decision\n- WhatsApp 428 flap: continues, harmless\n\n---\n\n## Apr 6 — Late Morning / Afternoon\n\n### Post 1 Live on Nava Corporate LinkedIn\n- Tiny revised the draft inline (rehab vs oncology contrast, 25% not double, \"Which is why we built NurseSphere\")\n- Screenshot confirmed at `Screenshot 2026-04-06 144532.png` — post live\n- Visual: split panel — \"Same number. Different worlds.\" — 8 stable vs 8 oncology patients\n- Added to corpus: `nava-corpus/linkedin-posts.md` + `rag/clean_txt/2026-04-06_navahc_linkedin_post_oncology_cna.md`\n- Link: `https://lnkd.in/dfXYNTRc`\n\n### NavaSM SKILL.md — Rewritten (committed)\n- Three personas (Yosef, Corporate, Tiny) — canonical, replacing five platform personas\n- Visual direction standard output — every post includes infographic concept\n- Concept-first → approval → draft workflow locked in\n- Competitor vocabulary section added: \"mail-sorting agencies,\" \"leaky bucket,\" \"volume trap,\" \"arbitrage,\" \"Reclaimix\"\n- Structural evaluation criteria added: contrast-before-abstract, concrete before abstract, CTA earned not bolted, every sentence does one job\n- Commit: `2d2415b`\n\n### MEMORY.md Updated — Structural Editing Principles\n- Contrast-before-abstract rule\n- Concrete-before-abstract rule\n- CTA earned principle\n- Every sentence does one job\n- Commit: `f0e6f92`\n\n### TOOLS.md — Screenshot Path Fixed\n- Path: `OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/` — Tiny's screenshots go here, NOT OpenClawScreenshots\n- Updated find command pattern for future reference\n- Commit: `2d2415b`\n\n### Travel Nursing Market Data — Key Numbers (Tiny's research via CustomGPT session)\n- 2019 pre-pandemic baseline: **$6.5 billion**, ~33,000 travelers\n- 2022 pandemic peak: **$44.6 billion**, ~175,000 travelers (430% volume increase)\n- 2024 current: **~$25 billion** (post-correction \"new normal\")\n- 2033 projection: **$90 billion** (total healthcare staffing market)\n- Wage inflation since 2019: only **~20%**\n- Key insight: 300% market growth vs 20% wage growth = \"State Change\" — structural shift from permanent to contingent workforce\n- CRITICAL: \"$39B without context is just a random number\" — always use $6.5B → $25B frame\n\n### Global Demographic Context\n- Japan: \"super-ageing\" society already in crisis\n- UK: strained wards, aging population\n- By 2030: 1 in 6 people globally will be over 60\n- US: 65+ population will drive 50% of all healthcare spending by end of decade\n\n### CustomGPT Session — Key Lessons for NavaSM\n1. No \"Volume God\" — Tiny banned this phrase, already done before\n2. Real numbers with context — \"$39B without context is just a random number\"\n3. Tiny is not a mouthpiece for Nava — post = his thoughts, Nava is context, not the other way around\n4. Discussion over promotion — start a conversation, not close one\n5. Global aging population — not just US\n6. Wichita is in the corporate post — personal post does not need to re-prove it\n7. CustomGPT pushed back (\"I don't see the actual growth here!\") before drafting — I should demand data before writing, not write then fix\n\n### Tiny's Personal Post — Draft Written\n- Used $6.5B → $25B → 300% growth vs 20% wage frame\n- \"State Change\" framing — permanent to contingent workforce\n- Global demographic context (Japan, UK, 1 in 6 over 60 by 2030)\n- Discussion opener at close\n- UK English, no em-dashes, punctuation outside quotes\n- Pending Tiny review + approval before posting\n\n### Screenshot Locations (permanent reference)\n- Tiny's manual screenshots: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive/Pictures/Screenshots 1/`\n- My automation screenshots: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OpenClawScreenshots/`\n- Find command: `find /mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/OneDrive -maxdepth 5 -name \"Screenshot 2026-04-06*\" 2>/dev/null`\n- Gemma analysis: use `gemma3:27b-cloud` via Python/urllib (base64 encoded image input)\n\n### WhatsApp 428 Flapping — Continues\n- Still happening periodically (499 and 428)\n- Harmless, reconnects automatically\n- Not resolved — ongoing issue\n\n---\n\n## Apr 6 — Evening Sprint Checkpoint (17:43 UTC)\n\n### Today's Wins\n- Post 1 live on Nava Corporate LinkedIn ✅\n- Tiny's personal post live ✅ (data scientist voice, $6.5B→$25B frame, global demographics)\n- NavaSM SKILL.md fully rewritten ✅ (three personas, visual direction, concept-first workflow)\n- MEMORY.md updated with structural editing principles ✅\n- TOOLS.md screenshot path fixed ✅\n- Both posts added to corpus ✅\n\n### Travel Nursing Market Data — Verified Numbers\n- 2019: $6.5B (pre-pandemic baseline, SIA)\n- 2022: $42.7B (pandemic peak, SIA)\n- 2023: $25.2B (post-correction, SIA)\n- 2024: $39.46B (current, datahorizzonresearch.com)\n- 2033: $71.81B (projection, datahorizzonresearch.com)\n- Wage inflation since 2019: ~20% (abstaffing.com)\n- Key frame: 300%+ market growth vs 20% wage growth = \"State Change\"\n- CRITICAL: \"$39B without context is just a random number\" — always use $6.5B → $25B frame for personal posts\n\n### TrnsBank\n- Count: check running\n\n---\n\n## Apr 6 — Evening Sprint Checkpoint (18:03 UTC)\n\n### X Post Draft — Final Structure\nThree-tweet arc for Nava Corporate X account:\n- **Tweet 1 (Twist):** Travel nurses caught a stray bullet — the system failed them, they get blamed\n- **Tweet 2 (Critique):** Travel nursing industry monetized the chaos — they need the problem to persist, 32-65% markup, arbitrage cycle\n- **Tweet 3 (Data + question):** $6.5B → $39B → 300% growth vs 20% wages = state change + discussion opener (longer because reader is invested)\n\n### Facebook Post — Live (Apr 6)\n- URL: https://navahc.com/international-nurse-recruitment/\n- Key techniques: Semicolons for parallel scenes, \"we\" implicates reader, \"may not\" hedge, extended closer to attrition arc, \"perhaps caring a little less\" understatement\n- Live post screenshot: Screenshot 2026-04-06 210344.png\n\nKey lesson learned: The \"twist\" structure — catch them off guard first, then reveal the mechanism — is more effective than leading with the data.\n\n### Current Status\n- Post 1 LI (Corporate): LIVE ✅\n- Post 1 LI (Tiny personal): LIVE ✅\n- Post 1 X (3-tweet): Drafted, awaiting Tiny's final approval for posting\n- Post 1 FB: LIVE ✅ (Nava Corporate Facebook, screenshot Screenshot 2026-04-06 210344.png)\n- Post 2: NavaSM draft delivered, awaiting Tiny review\n- Post 3: Not started\n- NavaSM SKILL.md: Rewritten and committed ✅\n\n### Key Lessons Learned Today (Apr 6)\n1. Thread structure: catch reader off guard first (twist), then reveal mechanism\n2. Emoji in thread headers: UX signal (\"keep scrolling\"), not emotional expression\n3. X/thread: each tweet is a chapter, not a standalone\n4. Facebook: semicolons for parallel scenes, \"we\" implicates reader\n5. Facebook closer: extend from one event to profession's attrition arc\n6. Understatement beats melodrama: \"perhaps caring a little less\" lands harder than melodramatic alternatives\n7. \"May not\" hedge: acknowledge other side before pivoting\n8. Earned numbers: verified figures over rounded approximations (27% not 20%)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775573295516}}
