{"type":"message","id":"b0d06c69","parentId":"af44c3d7","timestamp":"2026-04-07T17:36:42.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the revised prompt:\n\n---\n\n**Deep Research Prompt — Healthcare Staffing: The Full Financial Picture**\n\n---\n\nYou are a financial analyst producing a research brief for a healthcare content team. The goal: find verifiable financial data — disclosed in public filings, earnings calls, government records, and industry reports — that proves how the US healthcare staffing model extracts value from facilities at every level, and what the structural fix looks like in practice.\n\n**Tier 1 — Staffing Agencies (Public Filings)**\n\nSources: SEC 10-K/10-Q filings, earnings call transcripts, SIA annual reports.\n\nPrioritise:\n- AMN Healthcare, Cross Country Healthcare, CHG Healthcare, Aya Healthcare, Prestige Staffing\n- Revenue, gross margin, and EBITDA margin per firm, year-on-year (2022-2024)\n- Bill rate vs. nurse pay spread — the actual disclosed or derivable markup\n- Exact exec language connecting nurse shortage severity to pricing power or margin expansion\n- Travel/staffing segment margins specifically (not blended across business lines)\n- Market concentration — top 5 firms' share of the $47B market\n\n**Tier 2 — Hospital Systems (10-K / Annual Reports)**\n\nSources: SEC filings for HCA Healthcare, Tenet Healthcare, CommonSpirit Health, UHS; Kaufmann Hall hospital profitability reports.\n\nPrioritise:\n- Contract labor as a disclosed cost line — year-on-year spend and as % of total revenue\n- Margin improvement correlated with contract labor reduction (Kaufmann Hall already flags this)\n- Any 10-K language describing strategic shift away from agency toward permanent staff\n- ICU overtime data, agency spend per Adjusted Patient Day — granular staffing metrics disclosed\n- CFO commentary on staffing model sustainability in earnings calls\n\n**Tier 3 — LTC Facilities (CMS Cost Reports + PE Filings)**\n\nSources: CMS Medicare Cost Report data (cms.gov), 10-K filings for publicly traded LTC chains (Brookdale Senior Living, Genesis HealthCare), state regulatory filings for private chains.\n\nPrioritise:\n- Agency nurse spend per facility per year — actual dollar amounts from cost reports\n- Revenue per patient day vs. cost per patient day with agency vs. permanent breakdown\n- PE-owned chains' staffing model disclosures — any shift to domestic vs. international pipeline\n- State-specific LTC cost data showing agency markup impact at facility level\n\n**Tier 4 — Government / Public Facilities (VA, County, Federal)**\n\nSources: VA workforce reports, GAO reports on nurse staffing, SAMHSA data, state department of health public records, congressional testimony.\n\nPrioritise:\n- VA nursing shortage and contract labor spend data\n- GAO findings on agency nurse spend in federal facilities\n- Federal legislation on healthcare staffing (rate caps, disclosure requirements)\n- Any documented results from government facilities reducing agency spend\n\n**Cross-Cutting Angles**\n\nAlso surface:\n- State rate-cap legislation results — actual rate data before/after implementation (California, Oregon, Illinois, Massachusetts, and the 8 other states with active bills)\n- The $39-47B market size broken down by segment (travel nursing vs. per diem vs. LTC vs. allied)\n- Any academic or think-tank research on staffing agency margin expansion vs. nurse wage growth (the spread — what agencies kept vs. what went to nurses)\n\n**What to avoid:**\n- Industry association publications as primary sources (SIA is acceptable; anything funded by agencies is not)\n- Vague \"industry data\" without a named document\n- Any claim that cannot be traced to a named, verifiable source\n\n**Format:**\nStatement of Trade — factual, source-backed, organised by Tier. Each statistic should note its source document, page or exhibit reference where applicable. Flag clearly where data is thin, contested, or paywalled. Note any discrepancies between executive public statements and what the filings show.\n\n---\n\nThat's the full scope. Ready to fire it at Gemini, or do you want to add or cut anything before we run it?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":48474,"output":844,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775583402686}}
{"type":"message","id":"f994f6a7","parentId":"b0d06c69","timestamp":"2026-04-07T17:44:36.736Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-04-07 19:44 GMT+2] Ok, we have the research in downloads. I skimmed it and I suspect it is a goldmine worth maybe more than one post. Take a look and tell me what you think."}],"timestamp":1775583876718}}
