oach, including the metadata. Revising Strategic Choices I'm now zeroing in on the misconception that EB-3 and TN visas are mutually exclusive options, which is coming up in HR meetings. This false binary obscures the real question: which staffing pathway aligns be\n\n=== 60k ===\ns broader facility footprint while keeping the \"mortgage vs. hotel\" logic intact. Shall I proceed with those adjustments? You said Update the draft in the necessary places. Note that I made some minor changes of my own so it is imperative that you read what's on the canvas first before you make your\n\n=== 80k ===\nof a link mentioning lost revenue. I've also observed adjustments to vacancy cost phrasing and a change in the title of Section 3, along with several revisions in ROW Filing and India Backlog sections. Examining Key Edits I've just finished reviewing the edits and I can tell that there's a definite","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775583990336}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e756a51","parentId":"09a12c25","timestamp":"2026-04-07T17:46:45.042Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_6f0754fe-fcf6-498a-913f-729dcdb59dbe","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport re\n\ndef extract_text_from_html(path):\n    with open(path, encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    content = re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', content, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    content = re.sub(r'<style[^>]*>.*?</style>', '', content, flags=re.DOTALL)\n    content = re.sub(r'<[^>]+>', ' ', content)\n    content = re.sub(r'&nbsp;', ' ', content)\n    content = re.sub(r'&amp;', '&', content)\n    content = re.sub(r'&lt;', '<', content)\n    content = re.sub(r'&gt;', '>', content)\n    content = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', content)\n    return content\n\n# Search both HTML files for staffing/financial research keywords\nkeywords = ['gross margin', 'bill rate', 'markup', 'EBITDA', 'operating margin', \n            'staffing revenue', 'Kaufmann Hall', 'cost report', '10-K', \n            'travel nursing revenue', 'segment margin', 'state rate cap',\n            'hospital profit', 'agency spend', 'permanent nurse']\n\nfor fname in ['Gemini.html', 'NewGemini.html']:\n    path = f'/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/{fname}'\n    text = extract_text_from_html(path)\n    found = []\n    for kw in keywords:\n        idx = text.lower().find(kw.lower())\n        if idx != -1:\n            found.append(f\"  '{kw}' at {idx}: ...{text[max(0,idx-50):idx+150]}...\")\n    if found:\n        print(f\"\\n=== {fname} ===\")\n        for f in found[:5]:\n            print(f)\nPYEOF","timeout":15}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":61766,"output":691,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62457,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775584005040}}
{"type":"message","id":"efe98284","parentId":"1e756a51","timestamp":"2026-04-07T17:46:45.430Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_6f0754fe-fcf6-498a-913f-729dcdb59dbe","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Gemini.html ===\n  'markup' at 1984: ...em. Here's the cycle: hospitals pay 32-65% agency markups. Permanent nurses leave because travelers earn double for the same work. Hospitals can't afford the raises that might bring them back. So they...\n  'travel nursing revenue' at 43698: ...elations. Analyzing Market Trends The analysis of travel nursing revenue and demographic shifts forms a baseline for future considerations. Refining Calculations The recent focus is on incorporating \"...\n  'agency spend' at 3422: ...t (text-based) showing the \"Death Spiral\": Higher Agency Spend -> Permanent Staff Resentment -> More Resignations -> Higher Agency Spend. Option B: The Structural Critique (Nava Corporate Persona) Foc...\n  'permanent nurse' at 1993: ...s the cycle: hospitals pay 32-65% agency markups. Permanent nurses leave because travelers earn double for the same work. Hospitals can't afford the raises that might bring them back. So they travel m..."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":358,"aggregated":"=== Gemini.html ===\n  'markup' at 1984: ...em. Here's the cycle: hospitals pay 32-65% agency markups. Permanent nurses leave because travelers earn double for the same work. Hospitals can't afford the raises that might bring them back. So they...\n  'travel nursing revenue' at 43698: ...elations. Analyzing Market Trends The analysis of travel nursing revenue and demographic shifts forms a baseline for future considerations. Refining Calculations The recent focus is on incorporating \"...\n  'agency spend' at 3422: ...t (text-based) showing the \"Death Spiral\": Higher Agency Spend -> Permanent Staff Resentment -> More Resignations -> Higher Agency Spend. Option B: The Structural Critique (Nava Corporate Persona) Foc...\n  'permanent nurse' at 1993: ...s the cycle: hospitals pay 32-65% agency markups. Permanent nurses leave because travelers earn double for the same work. Hospitals can't afford the raises that might bring them back. So they travel m...","cwd":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775584005421}}
