{"type":"message","id":"2fb0315b","parentId":"6f60fee6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T18:04:50.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Right on both counts. The NurseSphere line is tired — I've used it too often. And Reclaimix deserves its own name in this closer because it's the actual answer to the problem the whole post describes.\n\nTry this:\n\n---\n\nThese are not systems failing to solve a problem. They are systems recognising that the problem is the model. Exactly as designed.\n\nThe facilities that have done the work are not going back. Reclaimix — Nava's conversion programme — eliminates the markup layer entirely by converting agency nurses into permanent staff. No third party. No spread. No green arrow on someone else's slide deck.\n\nThe model was never built for you. Nava built something that was.\n\n---\n\nOr if you want the CTA tighter:\n\n---\n\nThese are not systems failing to solve a problem. They are systems recognising that the problem is the model. Exactly as designed.\n\nReclaimix is the structural exit. It converts agency nurses into permanent staff, removes the markup, and stops the cycle. The question is not whether the model is broken. It is whether you are ready to stop being part of it.\n\n---\n\nWhich closer do you prefer?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":70697,"output":354,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71051,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775585090914}}
