{"type":"message","id":"2b0f3fc9","parentId":"da8bd67b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:31:27.351Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what TinyQE says:\n\n**Thesis Clarity (medium priority)**\nMultiple competing theses detected — the post is trying to explain the spread mechanic AND make the \"working as designed\" argument AND cite hospital exits as evidence, all at once. It needs to pick one central claim and let everything else serve it.\n\n**Readability Floor (medium priority)**\nFKGL of 5.3 — TinyQE thinks the text is too simple for the target audience (CFOs, facility leaders). LinkedIn B2B register should sit around FKGL 10-14. I overcorrected on the simplification. The fix isn't dumbing it down — it's raising the register while keeping it direct.\n\n**Evidence Quality (low priority)**\nSome claims lack statistical backing — the UHS/HCA/Tenet section is the weakest here.\n\n---\n\nMy read: the thesis point is valid. Tweet 2 is doing three things — explaining the spread, citing the California rates, and citing AMN's margins. Pick two, not three. And the hospital exit point in Tweet 3 is doing real work but needs to be foreshadowed earlier.\n\nThe readability note is interesting — TinyQE is saying LinkedIn B2B readers expect a higher cognitive load than my rewrite delivered. Useful signal.\n\nWant me to revise based on this, or do you have your own feedback first?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":45142,"output":544,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45686,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775597487348}}
