{"type":"message","id":"d755f90f","parentId":"a3cc65ec","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:50:02.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now fix proportionality to respect the social media mode:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_53b52ea3-d90b-40e1-b6f6-7a35e343d66d","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nProportionality Analyzer (C3)\nEvaluates whether evidence is proportionate to claims.\n\nSOCIAL MEDIA MODE (LinkedIn, X, copywriting):\n- Claims are understood to be illustrative, not peer-reviewed\n- Only truly extraordinary claims (health/safety superlatives, financial guarantees) require strong evidence\n- \"Working as designed,\" \"not built for you,\" structural critiques = normal social media register\n- Examples and logic count as acceptable evidence\n\nBLOG/ESSAY MODE:\n- Extraordinary claims require extraordinary evidence\n- Proportionality matters strictly\n\"\"\"\nimport re\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, List\n\n# ─── Truly extraordinary claims (social media) ─────────────────────────────────\n# These claims are so strong they would require verification even in social media.\n# Flag only these — not ordinary assertions about business models or systems.\nSOCIAL_EXTRAORDINARY = [\n    r'\\bcures\\b.*\\bcancer\\b', r'\\beliminates\\b.*\\bdisease\\b', r'\\bguaranteed\\s+profits?\\b',\n    r'\\brisk[\\-\\s]free\\s+investment\\b', r'\\b100%\\s+safe\\b', r'\\bproven\\s+to\\s+kill\\b',\n    r'\\bcauses\\s+autism\\b', r'\\binstant\\s+results?\\s+guaranteed\\b', r'\\bwill\\s+definitely\\b',\n    r'\\bpermanent\\s+cure\\b', r'\\balways\\s+works\\b', r'\\bnever\\s+fails\\b',\n    r'\\bsafe\\s+for\\s+everyone\\b', r'\\bno\\s+side\\s+effects?\\b', r'\\bmiracle\\s+(cure|treatment|drug)\\b',\n    r'\\bdeadly\\b.*\\bunless\\b', r'\\bkills\\b.*\\bguaranteed\\b'\n]\n\n# ─── Extraordinary claims (academic/blog) ────────────────────────────────────────\nEXTRAORDINARY_CLAIM_INDICATORS = [\n    r'\\bwill\\b.*\\brevolutionize\\b', r'\\bwill\\b.*\\btransform\\b', r'\\bwill\\b.*\\bchange\\s+everything\\b',\n    r'\\bnever\\b.*\\bbefore\\b', r'\\balways\\b', r'\\bnever\\b', r'\\bguaranteed\\b', r'\\b100%\\b', r'\\bperfect\\b',\n    r'\\bbest\\b.*\\bin\\b.*\\bthe\\b.*\\bworld\\b', r'\\bworst\\b.*\\bin\\b.*\\bthe\\b.*\\bworld\\b',\n    r'\\bbreakthrough\\b', r'\\bgame[\\-\\s]?changer\\b', r'\\bparadigm\\s+shift\\b', r'\\bmiracle\\b',\n    r'\\bcure\\b', r'\\beliminate\\b.*\\bproblem\\b', r'\\bsolve\\b.*\\bforever\\b',\n    r'\\bend\\b.*\\b\\w+\\s+once\\s+and\\s+for\\s+all\\b', r'\\bthe\\s+only\\b\\s+way\\b', r'\\bno\\s+more\\b',\n    r'\\bnever\\s+again\\b', r'\\bthis\\s+will\\s+change\\b.*\\bforever\\b', r'\\binstantly\\b',\n    r'\\bimmediately\\b', r'\\bwithin\\s+24\\s+hours\\b', r'\\bresults\\s+guaranteed\\b'\n]\n\nMODERATE_CLAIM_INDICATORS = [\n    r'\\bcan\\b.*\\bhelp\\b', r'\\bmay\\b.*\\bimprove\\b', r'\\btends\\s+to\\b', r'\\boften\\b.*\\bleads\\s+to\\b',\n    r'\\busually\\b', r'\\bgenerally\\b', r'\\bfrequently\\b', r'\\bcommonly\\b', r'\\btypically\\b',\n    r'\\bimproves\\b.*\\bby\\b', r'\\bincreases\\b.*\\bby\\b', r'\\bdecreases\\b.*\\bby\\b', r'\\breduces\\b.*\\bby\\b',\n    r'\\bsignificant\\b.*\\bimprovement\\b', r'\\bnoticeable\\b.*\\bchange\\b', r'\\bsubstantial\\b.*\\benefit\\b',\n    r'\\bbetter\\s+than\\b', r'\\bmore\\s+effective\\b\\s+than\\b'\n]\n\nWEAK_CLAIM_INDICATORS = [\n    r'\\bmight\\b', r'\\bcould\\b', r'\\bpossible\\b', r'\\bpossibly\\b', r'\\bperhaps\\b', r'\\bmaybe\\b',\n    r'\\bsuggests\\b', r'\\bindicates\\b', r'\\bappears\\b', r'\\bseems\\b', r'\\blikely\\b', r'\\bprobably\\b',\n    r'\\bassociated\\s+with\\b', r'\\blinked\\s+to\\b', r'\\bcorrelated\\s+with\\b', r'\\brelated\\s+to\\b',\n    r'\\bmay\\s+contribute\\b', r'\\bcould\\s+play\\s+a\\s+role\\b', r'\\bone\\s+factor\\s+is\\b', r'\\baspect\\s+of\\b'\n]\n\n# ─── Evidence indicators ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSTRONG_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS = [\n    r'randomized\\s+controlled\\s+trial', r'\\brct\\b', r'\\bmeta[\\-\\s]analysis\\b',\n    r'\\bsystematic\\s+review\\b', r'\\bdouble[\\-\\s]blind\\b', r'\\blongitudinal\\s+study\\b',\n    r'\\bcohort\\s+study\\b', r'\\bcase[\\-\\s]control\\s+study\\b', r'\\bp\\s*<\\s*0\\.001\\b',\n    r'\\bp\\s*<\\s*0\\.01\\b', r'\\bconfidence\\s+interval\\b', r'\\bn\\s*=\\s*\\d{3,}\\b',\n    r'\\bsample\\s+size\\b.*\\d{3,}\\b', r'\\bmulticenter\\b', r'\\bpeer[\\-\\s]?reviewed\\b',\n    r'\\bjournal\\b', r'\\bstudy\\s+of\\b.*\\b\\d{3,}\\s+participants\\b', r'\\bfollow[\\-\\s]up\\b.*\\b\\d+\\s+(years?|months?)\\b'\n]\n\nMODERATE_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS = [\n    r'\\bp\\s*<\\s*0\\.05\\b', r'\\bn\\s*=\\s*\\d{2,}\\b', r'\\bsample\\s+size\\b.*\\d{2,}\\b',\n    r'\\bpreliminary\\s+study\\b', r'\\bpilot\\s+study\\b', r'\\bobservational\\s+study\\b',\n    r'\\bcorrelational\\s+study\\b', r'\\bsurvey\\b', r'\\bquestionnaire\\b', r'\\binterview\\b',\n    r'\\bfocus\\s+group\\b', r'\\bcase\\s+report\\b', r'\\bcase\\s+series\\b', r'\\bretrospective\\s+analysis\\b',\n    r'\\bprospective\\s+analysis\\b', r'\\bchart\\s+review\\b'\n]\n\nWEAK_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS = [\n    r'\\banecdotal\\b', r'\\bcase\\s+example\\b', r'\\btestimonial\\b', r'\\bopinion\\b', r'\\bbelief\\b',\n    r'\\bthink\\b', r'\\bfeel\\b', r'\\bi\\s+believe\\b', r'\\bi\\s+think\\b', r'\\bmy\\s+experience\\b',\n    r'\\bone\\s+time\\b', r'\\bonce\\b', r'\\bin\\s+my\\s+practice\\b', r'\\bin\\s+my\\s+clinic\\b', r'\\bhearsay\\b',\n    r'\\bword\\s+of\\s+mouth\\b', r'\\brumor\\b', r'\\bspeculation\\b', r'\\bconjecture\\b', r'\\bguess\\b',\n    r'\\bpossibly\\b', r'\\bperhaps\\b', r'\\bmight\\b', r'\\bcould\\b', r'\\bsuggests\\b', r'\\bindicates\\b'\n]\n\n\ndef is_social_media_mode(format_profile: Dict = None, format_hint: str = \"\") -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if social media lenient mode should apply.\"\"\"\n    if format_profile and format_profile.get(\"social_media_mode\"):\n        return True\n    if format_hint in [\"linkedin\", \"x_thread\", \"copywriting\"]:\n        return True\n    return False\n\n\ndef assess_social_media_claims(text_lower: str) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    For social media: only flag truly extraordinary claims.\n    Returns (claim_strength, extraordinary_found, flag_detail)\n    \"\"\"\n    extraordinary_found = []\n    for pattern in SOCIAL_EXTRAORDINARY:\n        matches = re.findall(pattern, text_lower)\n        extraordinary_found.extend(matches)\n\n    if extraordinary_found:\n        return (\"extraordinary_social\", extraordinary_found)\n\n    # In social media mode, most business/structural claims are normal register\n    # No extraordinary indicators means claim strength = moderate by default\n    return (\"moderate\", [])\n\n\ndef assess_academic_claims(text_lower: str) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"For blog/essay: assess claim strength using full extraordinary scale.\"\"\"\n    extraordinary_score = sum(1 for p in EXTRAORDINARY_CLAIM_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n    moderate_score = sum(1 for p in MODERATE_CLAIM_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n    weak_score = sum(1 for p in WEAK_CLAIM_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n\n    if extraordinary_score > 0:\n        return (\"extraordinary\", extraordinary_score)\n    elif moderate_score > 0:\n        return (\"moderate\", moderate_score)\n    elif weak_score > 0:\n        return (\"weak\", weak_score)\n    else:\n        return (\"moderate\", 0)  # Default\n\n\ndef assess_evidence(text_lower: str) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"Assess evidence strength in text.\"\"\"\n    strong = sum(1 for p in STRONG_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n    moderate = sum(1 for p in MODERATE_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n    weak = sum(1 for p in WEAK_EVIDENCE_INDICATORS if re.search(p, text_lower))\n\n    if strong > 0:\n        return (\"strong\", strong)\n    elif moderate > 0:\n        return (\"moderate\", moderate)\n    elif weak > 0:\n        return (\"weak\", weak)\n    else:\n        # In social media mode, logical reasoning and examples count\n        logic_indicators = [\n            r'\\bbecause\\b', r'\\btherefore\\b', r'\\bconsequently\\b', r'\\bfor\\s+example\\b',\n            r'\\bfor\\s+instance\\b', r'\\bspecifically\\b', r'\\bin\\s+practice\\b', r'\\bdata\\b',\n            r'\\bpercent\\b', r'\\b\\$\\d', r'\\b\\$', r'\\b\\d+%\\b', r'\\b\\$\\d+\\s+million\\b',\n            r'\\bbillion\\b', r'\\bequals\\b', r'\\bthe\\s+math\\b', r'\\bthe\\s+number\\b',\n            r'\\bearnings\\b', r'\\brevenue\\b', r'\\bmargin\\b', r'\\bbenchmark\\b'\n        ]\n        logic_score = sum(1 for p in logic_indicators if re.search(p, text_lower))\n        if logic_score >= 2:\n            return (\"moderate\", logic_score)  # Logic + data = acceptable evidence for social\n        return (\"weak\", 0)\n\n\ndef analyze(text: str, format_hint: str = \"generic\", format_profile: Dict = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Main entry point.\n    Returns score 0.0-1.0 where 1.0 = excellent proportionality.\n    Social media mode: lenient, only flags truly extraordinary claims.\n    Academic/blog mode: strict, full extraordinary claim detection.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"dimension\": \"C3\",\n            \"dimension_name\": \"Proportionality\",\n            \"score\": 0.0,\n            \"verdict\": \"fail\",\n            \"confidence\": 0.9,\n            \"evidence\": [{\"passage\": \"\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"No text provided\", \"severity\": \"error\"}],\n            \"interpretation\": \"Empty text.\",\n            \"recommendation\": \"Provide content to evaluate.\"\n        }\n\n    text_lower = text.lower()\n    social_mode = is_social_media_mode(format_profile, format_hint)\n\n    # Assess claims\n    if social_mode:\n        claim_strength, extraordinary_found = assess_social_media_claims(text_lower)\n    else:\n        claim_strength, _ = assess_academic_claims(text_lower)\n\n    # Assess evidence\n    evidence_strength, _ = assess_evidence(text_lower)\n\n    # Weight mapping\n    claim_weight_map = {\"extraordinary\": 3.0, \"extraordinary_social\": 2.5, \"moderate\": 2.0, \"weak\": 1.0}\n    evidence_weight_map = {\"strong\": 3.0, \"moderate\": 2.0, \"weak\": 1.0, \"none\": 0.0}\n\n    claim_weight = claim_weight_map.get(claim_strength, 2.0)\n    evidence_weight = evidence_weight_map.get(evidence_strength, 1.0)\n\n    # Calculate proportionality\n    max_weight = 3.0\n    weight_diff = abs(evidence_weight - claim_weight)\n    score = max(0.0, 1.0 - (weight_diff / max_weight))\n\n    # In social media mode, give extra credit for having ANY evidence\n    if social_mode and evidence_weight >= 1.5 and claim_weight <= 2.5:\n        score = max(score, 0.7)  # Floor of 0.7 for reasonable social media posts\n    # In academic mode, score stays strict\n    elif not social_mode and evidence_weight == 0 and claim_weight > 0:\n        score = 0.0  # Fail if making claims with no evidence\n\n    score = round(score, 3)\n\n    # Verdict\n    if score >= 0.8:\n        verdict = \"pass\"\n    elif score >= 0.5:\n        verdict = \"warning\"\n    else:\n        verdict = \"fail\"\n\n    confidence = 0.85 if social_mode else 0.7\n\n    # Evidence list\n    evidence_list = []\n    evidence_list.append({\n        \"passage\": f\"Claim strength assessed as: {claim_strength}\",\n        \"location\": \"document\",\n        \"signal\": f\"Claim strength: {claim_strength}\",\n        \"severity\": \"info\"\n    })\n    evidence_list.append({\n        \"passage\": f\"Evidence strength assessed as: {evidence_strength}\",\n        \"location\": \"document\",\n        \"signal\": f\"Evidence strength: {evidence_strength}\",\n        \"severity\": \"info\"\n    })\n    if social_mode and extraordinary_found:\n        evidence_list.append({\n            \"passage\": str(extraordinary_found[:3]),\n            \"location\": \"document\",\n            \"signal\": \"Truly extraordinary claim detected (social media mode)\",\n            \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        })\n\n    # Interpretation\n    mode_label = \"social media\" if social_mode else \"academic/blog\"\n    if verdict == \"pass\":\n        interpretation = f\"[{mode_label}] Evidence strength ({evidence_strength}) is proportionate to claim strength ({claim_strength}).\"\n        recommendation = \"Evidence proportionality is appropriate for the format.\"\n    elif verdict == \"warning\":\n        if evidence_weight > claim_weight:\n            interpretation = f\"[{mode_label}] Evidence may be stronger than needed.\"\n            recommendation = \"Consider whether the evidence exceeds what's needed.\"\n        else:\n            interpretation = f\"[{mode_label}] Evidence may be thin for the claims made, but acceptable for this format.\"\n            if social_mode:\n                recommendation = \"Social media claims don't require academic-level evidence. Consider whether any claims need a data point or example to land.\"\n            else:\n                recommendation = \"Strengthen evidence or temper claims.\"\n    else:\n        interpretation = f\"[{mode_label}] Evidence strength ({evidence_strength}) is insufficient for claim strength ({claim_strength}).\"\n        if social_mode:\n            recommendation = \"Add at least one data point, example, or logical anchor to support the main claim.\"\n        else:\n            recommendation = \"Strengthen evidence with data, studies, or examples, or temper claims to match available evidence.\"\n\n    return {\n        \"dimension\": \"C3\",\n        \"dimension_name\": \"Proportionality\",\n        \"score\": score,\n        \"verdict\": verdict,\n        \"confidence\": confidence,\n        \"evidence\": evidence_list,\n        \"interpretation\": interpretation,\n        \"recommendation\": recommendation\n    }\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        text = \" \".join(sys.argv[1:])\n    else:\n        text = sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    result = analyze(text)\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/proportionality.py"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":72070,"output":3736,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775598602482}}
{"type":"message","id":"667ad1f3","parentId":"d755f90f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:50:02.561Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_53b52ea3-d90b-40e1-b6f6-7a35e343d66d","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 12767 bytes to /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/proportionality.py"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775598602538}}
{"type":"message","id":"76a3fce0","parentId":"667ad1f3","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:51:02.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now fix structural_completeness to handle Tiny's hook pattern:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_6e1e2a6b-67b4-4e4b-9e4c-130dc7467626","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nStructural Completeness Analyzer (B3)\nChecks whether the argument has all necessary components:\nclaim → setup → evidence → complication → resolution (blog)\nhook → development → landing (short-form: LinkedIn, X, copywriting)\n\nSHORT-FORM HOOK RECOGNITION:\nA hook is NOT a thesis statement. A hook names a phenomenon or asks a question\nthat makes the reader want to know more — without giving away the argument.\nTypes that score a hook:\n  - Questions (rhetorical or genuine)\n  - Surprising statements / statistics\n  - Bold observational claims (creates curiosity)\n  - \"When X happens, [something unexpected]\" patterns\n  - Contradiction patterns (\"The industry celebrates X\")\n  - Pattern interruption (\"The thing nobody tells you about X\")\n\"\"\"\nimport re\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, List\n\n# ─── Hook detection patterns for short-form ────────────────────────────────────\n# A hook makes the reader click \"show more\" — it names a phenomenon, poses a\n# question, or states something surprising WITHOUT giving away the argument.\nHOOK_PATTERNS = {\n    \"question\": [r'\\?$', r'^what\\s+', r'^why\\s+', r'^how\\s+', r'^when\\s+', r'^if\\s+'],\n    \"observational_teaser\": [\n        r\"^when an industry\", r\"^what happens when\", r\"^here('s| is) the thing\",\n        r\"^what nobody\", r\"^the real\", r\"^the hidden\", r\"^the unspoken\",\n        r\"^the inconvenient\", r\"^what i learned\", r\"^what they don't\",\n        r\"^the secret\", r\"^the problem with\", r\"^the truth about\",\n        r\"^turns out\", r\"^it turns out\", r\"^surprising\", r\"^curiously\",\n        r\"^remarkably\", r\"^interestingly\", r\"^the fact is\",\n        r\"^the reality is\", r\"^the problem isn('t| not)\"\n    ],\n    \"contradiction\": [\n        r\"^while\\b\", r\"^although\\b\", r\"^but\\b\", r\"^yet\\b\",\n        r\"^they said\", r\"^the industry (celebrates|calls|calls it)\",\n        r\"^it('s| is) not.*but\", r\"^this.*isn('t| not) what\"\n    ],\n    \"stat_start\": [\n        r'^\\$[\\d,]+', r'^\\d+%', r'^\\d+\\s+(million|billion|thousand)',\n        r'^\\$\\d+\\s+million', r'^in\\s+\\d{4}', r'^in\\s+20\\d{2}'\n    ],\n    \"bold_claim\": [\n        r\"^the only\", r\"^never again\", r\"^no one\", r\"^everyone is\",\n        r\"^stop\\b\", r\"^never\\b\", r\"^always\\b\", r\"^you('re| are) not\",\n        r\"^this is (why|how|the)\", r\"^here('s| is) (why|what|how)\"\n    ]\n}\n\ndef detect_hook(paragraph: str) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns (is_hook: bool, hook_type: str, evidence: str)\n    \"\"\"\n    first_line = paragraph.strip().split('\\n')[0]  # First line only\n    first_lower = first_line.lower()\n\n    for hook_type, patterns in HOOK_PATTERNS.items():\n        for pattern in patterns:\n            if re.search(pattern, first_lower):\n                return (True, hook_type, first_line[:100])\n\n    # If no pattern matches, check for generic \"curiosity gap\" — short, declarative,\n    # implies something without stating it\n    words = len(first_line.split())\n    if words <= 20 and not first_line.endswith('.') and not first_line.endswith(':'):\n        return (True, \"minimal_curiosity\", first_line[:100])\n\n    return (False, \"\", \"\")\n\n\ndef analyze(text: str, format_hint: str = \"generic\", format_profile: Dict = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Main entry point.\n    LinkedIn/X: hook → development → landing.\n    Blog/essay: claim → setup → evidence → complication → resolution.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not text.strip():\n        return {\n            \"dimension\": \"B3\",\n            \"dimension_name\": \"Structural Completeness\",\n            \"score\": 0.0,\n            \"verdict\": \"fail\",\n            \"confidence\": 0.9,\n            \"evidence\": [{\"passage\": \"\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"No text provided\", \"severity\": \"error\"}],\n            \"interpretation\": \"Empty text.\",\n            \"recommendation\": \"Provide content to evaluate.\"\n        }\n\n    # Detect format\n    try:\n        sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"..\", \"core\"))\n        from format_detector import detect_format, load_format_profile\n    except ImportError:\n        import os\n        sys.path.insert(0, os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"..\", \"core\"))\n        from format_detector import detect_format, load_format_profile\n\n    fmt, _ = detect_format(text)\n    profile = load_format_profile(fmt) if format_profile is None else format_profile\n\n    paragraphs = re.split(r'\\n\\s*\\n', text.strip())\n    paragraphs = [p.strip() for p in paragraphs if p.strip()]\n\n    if not paragraphs:\n        return {\n            \"dimension\": \"B3\",\n            \"dimension_name\": \"Structural Completeness\",\n            \"score\": 0.0,\n            \"verdict\": \"fail\",\n            \"confidence\": 0.9,\n            \"evidence\": [{\"passage\": \"\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"No paragraphs found\", \"severity\": \"error\"}],\n            \"interpretation\": \"No discernible structure.\",\n            \"recommendation\": \"Organize content into paragraphs.\"\n        }\n\n    found = {k: False for k in [\"hook\", \"claim\", \"setup\", \"evidence\", \"complication\", \"resolution\", \"development\", \"landing\"]}\n    evidence = []\n\n    # ── SHORT-FORM (LinkedIn, X, copywriting) ───────────────────────────────────\n    if fmt in [\"linkedin\", \"x_thread\", \"copywriting\"]:\n\n        # HOOK: first paragraph — grab attention, make reader click \"show more\"\n        is_hook, hook_type, hook_text = detect_hook(paragraphs[0])\n        if is_hook:\n            found[\"hook\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\n                \"passage\": hook_text,\n                \"location\": \"paragraph 1 (opening)\",\n                \"signal\": f\"Hook detected (type: {hook_type})\",\n                \"severity\": \"info\"\n            })\n        else:\n            # Hook not detected — check if it's at least short/curious\n            if len(paragraphs[0].split()) <= 25:\n                found[\"hook\"] = True\n                evidence.append({\n                    \"passage\": paragraphs[0][:80],\n                    \"location\": \"paragraph 1 (opening)\",\n                    \"signal\": \"Possible minimal hook detected (short opening line)\",\n                    \"severity\": \"info\"\n                })\n            else:\n                evidence.append({\n                    \"passage\": paragraphs[0][:80],\n                    \"location\": \"paragraph 1\",\n                    \"signal\": \"Hook not clearly detected\",\n                    \"severity\": \"warning\"\n                })\n\n        # DEVELOPMENT: middle paragraphs build the argument\n        if len(paragraphs) >= 2:\n            found[\"development\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\n                \"passage\": f\"{len(paragraphs)-2} middle paragraphs\",\n                \"location\": f\"paragraphs 2-{len(paragraphs)-1}\",\n                \"signal\": \"Development present\",\n                \"severity\": \"info\"\n            })\n\n        # LANDING: last paragraph — CTA, resolution, or return to hook\n        last = paragraphs[-1].lower()\n        landing_phrases = [\n            \"that's why\", \"this is why\", \"learn more\", \"sign up\", \"get started\",\n            \"save this\", \"book a\", \"download\", \"try free\", \"start free\", \"free trial\",\n            \"click below\", \"comment\", \"share your\", \"questions\",\n            \"if you want\", \"reach out\", \"let me know\", \"connect with\",\n            \"ready to\", \"the facilities that have done\",\n            \"the model was never built\", \"the question for\", \"ask yourself\",\n            \"what is your\", \"what's your\"\n        ]\n        is_short_final = len(paragraphs[-1].split()) <= 10\n\n        if any(phrase in last for phrase in landing_phrases) or is_short_final:\n            found[\"landing\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\n                \"passage\": paragraphs[-1][:80],\n                \"location\": f\"paragraph {len(paragraphs)} (closing)\",\n                \"signal\": \"Landing detected\",\n                \"severity\": \"info\"\n            })\n        else:\n            # Check if it at least resolves/closes the argument\n            if paragraphs[-1].strip().endswith('.') and len(paragraphs[-1].split()) >= 5:\n                found[\"landing\"] = True\n                evidence.append({\n                    \"passage\": paragraphs[-1][:80],\n                    \"location\": f\"paragraph {len(paragraphs)} (closing)\",\n                    \"signal\": \"Landing/close detected (full stop ending)\",\n                    \"severity\": \"info\"\n                })\n            else:\n                evidence.append({\n                    \"passage\": paragraphs[-1][:80],\n                    \"location\": f\"paragraph {len(paragraphs)}\",\n                    \"signal\": \"Landing not clearly detected\",\n                    \"severity\": \"warning\"\n                })\n\n        required = [\"hook\", \"development\", \"landing\"]\n        missing = [r for r in required if not found[r]]\n\n    # ── LONG-FORM (blog, essay, academic) ─────────────────────────────────────\n    else:\n        full_text = ' '.join(paragraphs).lower()\n\n        # CLAIM: declarative thesis in first 2 paragraphs\n        claim_patterns = [\n            r'\\bis\\b', r'\\bare\\b', r'\\bwill\\b', r'\\bmust\\b', r'\\bshould\\b',\n            r'\\bcauses\\b', r'\\bleads to\\b', r'\\bshows that\\b',\n            r'\\bdemonstrates that\\b', r'\\bevidence suggests\\b', r'\\bstudy indicates\\b'\n        ]\n        for para in paragraphs[:2]:\n            for sent in re.split(r'[.!?]+', para):\n                if any(re.search(p, sent.lower()) for p in claim_patterns):\n                    found[\"claim\"] = True\n                    evidence.append({\"passage\": sent.strip()[:100], \"location\": \"early paragraphs\", \"signal\": \"Claim detected\", \"severity\": \"info\"})\n                    break\n            if found[\"claim\"]:\n                break\n\n        # SETUP: background, problem statement\n        setup_indicators = [\n            r'background', r'context', r'problem', r'challenge', r'issue',\n            r'situation', r'currently', r'today', r'in recent years',\n            r'according to', r'data shows', r'historically'\n        ]\n        if any(re.search(p, full_text) for p in setup_indicators):\n            found[\"setup\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\"passage\": \"Context or background detected\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"Setup detected\", \"severity\": \"info\"})\n\n        # EVIDENCE: data, examples, citations\n        evidence_indicators = [\n            r'\\d+%', r'\\d+\\.\\d+', r'according to', r'study', r'research',\n            r'data shows', r'p <', r'correlation', r'example', r'for instance',\n            r'case study', r'citation', r'reference', r'\\bdoi\\b', r'http', r'www\\.',\n            r'\\$[\\d,]+', r'\\$[\\d,]+ million', r'\\$[\\d,]+ billion'\n        ]\n        if any(re.search(p, full_text, re.IGNORECASE) for p in evidence_indicators):\n            found[\"evidence\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\"passage\": \"Data, examples, or citations detected\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"Evidence detected\", \"severity\": \"info\"})\n\n        # COMPLICATION: counterargument, limitation, obstacle\n        complication_indicators = [\n            r'however', r'but', r'alt\though', r'despite', r'yet', r'still',\n            r'nevertheless', r'despite this', r'on the other hand',\n            r'limitations', r'challenges remain', r'obstacles', r'drawbacks',\n            r'trade-off', r'cost', r'risk', r'concern'\n        ]\n        if any(re.search(p, full_text) for p in complication_indicators):\n            found[\"complication\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\"passage\": \"Counterargument or complication detected\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"Complication detected\", \"severity\": \"info\"})\n\n        # RESOLUTION: solution, recommendation, conclusion\n        resolution_indicators = [\n            r'therefore', r'thus', r'hence', r'as a result', r'in conclusion',\n            r'to summarize', r'we recommend', r'solution', r'resolve',\n            r'address', r'overcome', r'mitigate', r'future work', r'next steps'\n        ]\n        if any(re.search(p, full_text) for p in resolution_indicators):\n            found[\"resolution\"] = True\n            evidence.append({\"passage\": \"Resolution or conclusion detected\", \"location\": \"document\", \"signal\": \"Resolution detected\", \"severity\": \"info\"})\n\n        required = [\"claim\", \"evidence\", \"resolution\"]\n        missing = [r for r in required if not found[r]]\n\n    # ── SCORE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    found_required = sum(1 for r in required if found[r])\n    score = found_required / len(required) if required else 0.0\n    score = round(score, 3)\n\n    if score >= 0.8:\n        verdict = \"pass\"\n    elif score >= 0.5:\n        verdict = \"warning\"\n    else:\n        verdict = \"fail\"\n\n    confidence = 0.8\n\n    if not evidence:\n        evidence.append({\n            \"passage\": text[:100],\n            \"location\": \"document\",\n            \"signal\": \"No structural components clearly detected\",\n            \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        })\n\n    # ── INTERPRETATION ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    fmt_label = \"LinkedIn/X\" if fmt in [\"linkedin\", \"x_thread\", \"copywriting\"] else \"blog/essay\"\n\n    if verdict == \"pass\":\n        interpretation = f\"[{fmt_label}] Structure complete: {', '.join([r.upper() for r in required if found[r]])}.\"\n        recommendation = \"Structure is sound.\"\n    elif verdict == \"warning\":\n        missing_str = ', '.join([m.upper() for m in missing])\n        interpretation = f\"[{fmt_label}] Missing: {missing_str}.\"\n        if fmt in [\"linkedin\", \"x_thread\", \"copywriting\"]:\n            recommendation = \"Ensure your post has a hook (attention-grabber), development (elaboration), and landing (resolution/CTA).\"\n        else:\n            recommendation = \"Ensure your argument includes a clear claim, supporting evidence, and a resolution or conclusion.\"\n    else:\n        missing_str = ', '.join([m.upper() for m in missing])\n        interpretation = f\"[{fmt_label}] Structure incomplete. Missing: {missing_str}.\"\n        if fmt in [\"linkedin\", \"x_thread\", \"copywriting\"]:\n            recommendation = \"Add a clear hook, develop your point in middle paragraphs, and end with a landing.\"\n        else:\n            recommendation = \"Restructure to include: claim → setup → evidence → complication → resolution.\"\n\n    return {\n        \"dimension\": \"B3\",\n        \"dimension_name\": \"Structural Completeness\",\n        \"score\": score,\n        \"verdict\": verdict,\n        \"confidence\": confidence,\n        \"evidence\": evidence,\n        \"interpretation\": interpretation,\n        \"recommendation\": recommendation\n    }\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        text = \" \".join(sys.argv[1:])\n    else:\n        text = sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    import os, json as json_mod\n    profile_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"..\", \"config\", \"format_profiles\", \"linkedin.json\")\n    try:\n        with open(profile_path, 'r') as f:\n            profile = json_mod.load(f)\n    except:\n        profile = None\n    result = analyze(text)\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n","path":"/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/structural_completeness.py"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":75142,"output":3790,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78932,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775598662205}}
{"type":"message","id":"134ed23e","parentId":"76a3fce0","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:51:02.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_6e1e2a6b-67b4-4e4b-9e4c-130dc7467626","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 14862 bytes to /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/tinyqe/analyzers/structural_completeness.py"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775598662327}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee81c75b","parentId":"134ed23e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:51:13.648Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let's test all three on Tiny's actual post:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_b3635550-4ca0-4e8c-b6d3-88821c23a08d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace && python3 tinyqe/tinyqe.py --format json << 'POST'\nWhen an industry treats a nursing strike as a revenue line item, perhaps the system is working exactly as designed.\n\nHere is what that phrase actually means in practice. When hospitals face staffing shortages or nurses go on strike, they call an agency to fill those shifts. The agency charges a premium for the emergency coverage. AMN Healthcare calls that premium \"labor disruption revenue.\" On their February 2025 earnings call, CEO Cary Grace announced they beat their own projection on that line by $22 million. The strikes happened. They collected.\n\nThe spread between what agencies charge hospitals and what they pay nurses is where the margin lives. Cross Country Healthcare put it plainly on an earnings call: they manage bill rates to hospitals against nurse pay expectations. Those are the two blades of the same scissors, and the gap between them is not accidental. In California, contract nursing rates reached $116 per hour in 2023, up from $81 in 2019. That $35 escalation did not flow to nurses. It flowed to agency margins. AMN's gross margin in 2024 was 30.8% on $2.98 billion in revenue.\n\nHospital systems are now running from the model. Universal Health Services' CFO named it explicitly: lower premium labor is the core driver of their EBITDA growth. HCA is building internal nursing pipelines to stop paying agency markups. Tenet cut contract labor and absorbed a 200 basis point margin compression in the transition. The math only works because the alternative is worse.\n\nThese are not systems failing to solve a problem. They are systems recognising that the problem is the model. Exactly as designed.\n\nThis is why Nava operates on two parallel tracks. Reclaimix converts agency nurses already in your building into permanent staff — eliminating the markup on the people you depend on today. NurseSphere builds a multi-year international clinical baseline — so you stop renting strangers at crisis rates and start owning a workforce that knows your patients, your systems, and your team. The markup was never inevitable. It was a structural choice made by an industry that had no incentive to give you a better option. NaVa built both tracks because the crisis did not arrive from one direction, and neither does the exit.\n\nThe facilities that have done the work are not going back. The model was never built for you.\nPOST","timeout":30}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":76782,"output":563,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77345,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775598673646}}
{"type":"message","id":"b728bd2e","parentId":"ee81c75b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:51:14.432Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_b3635550-4ca0-4e8c-b6d3-88821c23a08d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"evaluation_id\": \"5e9a5b65-813b-4b69-87d7-b7371f50b1c0\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-07T21:51:14.377735Z\",\n  \"format_detected\": \"linkedin\",\n  \"format_confidence\": 0.85,\n  \"overall_snapshot\": {\n    \"weighted_score\": 0.76,\n    \"verdict\": \"warning\",\n    \"one_liner\": \"Strong thesis clarity; needs work on evidence quality, platform reach potential.\"\n  },\n  \"dimension_results\": [\n    {\n      \"dimension\": \"A1\",\n      \"dimension_name\": \"Linguistic Integrity\",\n      \"score\": 0.884,\n      \"verdict\": \"pass\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"e.\\\"\",\n          \"location\": \"char 390-393\",\n          \"signal\": \"missing space after period\",\n          \"severity\": \"error\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"an i\",\n          \"location\": \"char 5-9\",\n          \"signal\": \"use 'a' before consonant sound\",\n          \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"an a\",\n          \"location\": \"char 243-247\",\n          \"signal\": \"use 'a' before consonant sound\",\n          \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"an e\",\n          \"location\": \"char 701-705\",\n          \"signal\": \"use 'a' before consonant sound\",\n          \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"an i\",\n          \"location\": \"char 2080-2084\",\n          \"signal\": \"use 'a' before consonant sound\",\n          \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"interpretation\": \"9 mechanical errors detected. Highest priority: missing space after period\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Address errors in order: missing space after period, use 'a' before consonant sound, use 'a' before consonant sound\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"dimension\": \"A2\",\n      \"dimension_name\": \"Readability Floor\",\n      \"score\": 1.0,\n      \"verdict\": \"pass\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"FKGL: 7.6, FRE: 61.2, SMOG: 10.7\",\n          \"location\": \"document\",\n          \"signal\": \"Grade level 7.6 (optimal: 7.0-8.5)\",\n          \"severity\": \"info\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"interpretation\": \"Readability is appropriate for target audience (FKGL 7.6).\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"No changes needed for readability.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"dimension\": \"B1\",\n      \"dimension_name\": \"Thesis Clarity\",\n      \"score\": 0.5,\n      \"verdict\": \"warning\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"Here is what that phrase actually means in practice\",\n          \"location\": \"paragraph 2\",\n          \"signal\": \"Primary thesis candidate: 'Here is what that phrase actually means in practice...'\",\n          \"severity\": \"info\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"When hospitals face staffing shortages or nurses go on strike, they call an agency to fill those shifts\",\n          \"location\": \"paragraph 2\",\n          \"signal\": \"Secondary thesis candidate: 'When hospitals face staffing shortages or nurses go on strike, they call an agen...'\",\n          \"severity\": \"warning\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"Candidate 1 (from paragraph 2): 'Here is what that phrase actually means in practice...' || Candidate 2 (from paragraph 2): 'When hospitals face staffing shortages or nurses go on strike, they call an agen...' || Candidate 3 (from paragraph 2): 'The agency charges a premium for the emergency coverage...' || Candidate 4 (from paragraph 3): 'The spread between what agencies charge hospitals and what they pay nurses is wh...' || Candidate 5 (from paragraph 3): 'Cross Country Healthcare put it plainly on an earnings call: they manage bill ra...' || Candidate 6 (from paragraph 3): 'Those are the two blades of the same scissors, and the gap between them is not a...' || Candidate 7 (from paragraph 4): 'Hospital systems are now running from the model...' || Candidate 8 (from paragraph 4): 'Universal Health Services' CFO named it explicitly: lower premium labor is the c...' || Candidate 9 (from paragraph 4): 'HCA is building internal nursing pipelines to stop paying agency markups...' || Candidate 10 (from paragraph 5): 'These are not systems failing to solve a problem...' || Candidate 11 (from paragraph 5): 'They are systems recognising that the problem is the model...' || Candidate 12 (from paragraph 6): 'Reclaimix converts agency nurses already in your building into permanent staff \\u2014...' || Candidate 13 (from paragraph 6): 'NurseSphere builds a multi-year international clinical baseline \\u2014 so you stop re...' || Candidate 14 (from paragraph 6): 'The markup was never inevitable...'\",\n          \"location\": \"document\",\n          \"signal\": \"thesis_conflict_explanation\",\n          \"severity\": \"info\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"interpretation\": \"Multiple thesis-like statements detected. This may be intentional for the format.\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"For short-form (LinkedIn/X): the opening line is the hook+thesis combined. Body paragraphs develop it, they don't introduce new theses. For long-form: choose one central claim and ensure all content supports it.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"dimension\": \"B2\",\n      \"dimension_name\": \"Logical Flow\",\n      \"score\": 0.0,\n      \"verdict\": \"fail\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"passage\": \"Here is what that phrase actually means in practice.\",\n          \"location\": \"sentence 2\",\n          \"signal\": \"No clear transition to previous sentence\",\