{"type":"compaction","id":"6804b33b","parentId":"698e39ed","timestamp":"2026-04-07T22:08:56.847Z","summary":"## Decisions\n- **Post A pattern fix**: Removed \"that's not X, that's Y\" structure from Post A after Tiny flagged it; replaced with declarative statements (\"AMN keeps the spread,\" \"The model is working exactly as designed\")\n- **NavaSM skill rule to add**: Pattern should be added to NavaSM SKILL.md to prevent future recurrence\n- **TinyQE evaluation direction**: B2 (Logical Flow 0.0) and C3 (Proportionality 0.0) are the actionable failures — don't declare the verdict, show the evidence and let the reader conclude\n- **Readability correction**: Overcorrected on simplification — FKGL 5.3 is too simple for CFO audience; register should be raised while keeping it direct\n\n## Open TODOs\n- [ ] X posts: awaiting Tiny's pick from three drafts (Post A, B, or C) + any edits before posting\n- [ ] Post 3: not yet started\n- [ ] Add \"no 'that's not X, that's Y' pattern\" rule to NavaSM SKILL.md\n- [ ] TrnsBank: still at 175, waiting for Tiny lock signal (threshold 200)\n- [ ] LinkedIn browser relay for posting without phone — unresolved\n- [ ] Git remote origin missing — workspace not pushing to GitHub\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Follow NavaSM SKILL.md strictly (Three Personas: Yosef Roston, Nava Corporate, Tiny Manyonga)\n- **No \"that's not X, that's Y\" pattern** — confirmed dislike from Tiny, confirmed in Post A rewrite\n- TrnsBank: wait for Tiny lock signal before analysing (currently at 175, under 200 threshold)\n- UK/SA English for published content (\"realise\", \"specialist\", \"labour\")\n\n## Pending user asks\n1. Which X thread to post first — Post A, B, or C?\n2. Any edits to X threads before posting?\n3. Whether to revise Post A based on TinyQE feedback, or Tiny has own feedback first?\n4. Whether the emotional calibration edge is earned where it sits (answered)\n\n## Exact identifiers\n### Files/Paths\n- Workspace: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/`\n- Memory: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/`\n- Today memory: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-07.md`\n- NavaSM: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/skills/navasm/SKILL.md`\n- Post series: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/nava-linkedin-series/`\n- Post 2 file: `nava-linkedin-series/02_exactly_as_designed.md`\n- TrnsBank: `/home/tiny4lurv/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TrnsBank.md`\n- Primary research file: `/mnt/c/Users/Tiny4Lurv/Downloads/Healthcare Staffing Value Extraction Analysis.odt`\n\n### Session IDs\n- Current active session: `9a8bd3a9-82c2-4811-8e07-2a90c9ea64bb.jsonl` (last modified Apr 7 16:46)\n\n### URLs\n- X Post 1: https://x.com/NavaRecruitment/status/2041223844321538522\n- Git remote: https://github.com/tiny4lurv/dawn-workspace.git\n\n### Identifiers\n- Git Post 2 commit: `e650aa9`\n- TinyQE evaluation ID: `58ba84ab-43c7-42e1-872c-f06b9f6ed079`\n- WhatsApp number: `+27763674298`\n\n### TinyQE Scores (Post A fixed version)\n| Dimension | Score | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|\n| Overall | 0.739 | Actionable |\n| A1 Linguistic Integrity | 0.885 | pass |\n| A2 Readability Floor | **0.373** | **FAIL** |\n| B1 Thesis Clarity | 0.5 | warning |\n| B2 Logical Flow | **0.0** | **FAIL** |\n| B3 Structural Completeness | 0.667 | warning |\n| C1 Evidence Quality | 0.7 | warning |\n| C2 Argumentative Rigor | 0.8 | pass |\n| C3 Proportionality | **0.0** | **FAIL** |\n| D1 Authorial Voice | 0.913 | pass |\n| D2 Tone Consistency | 0.95 | pass |\n| D3 Emotional Calibration | 0.5 | warning |\n| E1 Platform Reach Potential | 0.97 | pass |\n\n### Three X Thread Drafts\n- **Post A — The $62M Thread** (analytical/clinical): AMN $62M hook, spread mechanic, hospital exits as signal\n- **Post B — The Rate Escalation Thread** (P&L math): $116/hour, $35 gap, oligopoly structure\n- **Post C — The Hospital Exit Thread** (CFO/strategic): UHS/HCA/Tenet simultaneous exit as structural signal\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n## Decisions\n- **Use Python logic changes over prompt engineering**: Assistant confirmed the model used to write code is irrelevant; changes require modifying Python analyzer logic, not LLM prompts\n- **Format-aware thesis detection**: Short-form (LinkedIn/X) treats opening line as hook+thesis combined; last paragraph is always the landing/CTA and excluded from thesis candidates\n- **Social media extraordinary bar raised**: Only truly extraordinary claims (health/safety superlatives, financial guarantees) flag in social media mode; \"working as designed,\" structural critiques, and business model observations are normal register\n- **Per-format proportionality scoring**: Social media mode gets a floor score of 0.7 when any evidence is present; academic/blog mode remains strict\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Fix **Structural Completeness (B3)** hook detection to recognize observational/teaser hooks (e.g., \"When an industry treats a nursing strike as a revenue line item\") — no question, no number, no \"how to,\" no \"secret\" pattern\n- Test all three modified analyzers against the user's LinkedIn post example\n- The user asked to be shown **why** the tool is not identifying the thesis correctly so they can fix it themselves\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- First line of LI posts must function as trailer/teaser (\"click show more\")\n- Tool must specify when it detects thesis conflicts with explanation of why\n- Social media posts: high tolerance for weak/no evidence; only flag truly unverifiable claims (beyond cursory Google search)\n- Social media claims are illustrative, not peer-reviewed\n\n## Pending user asks\n- The user explicitly requested: \"I want it to specify when it thinks there is a conflict in thesis. **Only when I understand why it is not identifying the reason why I post like this can I fix it.**\" — this goal is partially addressed in thesis_clarity.py via `thesis_conflict_explanation` signal but has not been confirmed as sufficient\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- File: `/home/tiny4lurv/.